<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="17.[189,1398,267,410]" box="[189,310,267,293]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,267,293]" fontSize="11" level="5" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" reason="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,267,293]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[189,1398,267,410]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
Easily separated from other species of the group by the large, plate-like juxta, with the base slightly fattened, without sclerotization, with a long and widening neck, ending on each side in a rounded apex, on both sides tufted with small-sized hairs (
<figureCitation box="[700,792,384,410]" captionStart="Fig. 2" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1873,1899]" captionTargetBox="[192,1392,424,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[181,1446,419,1845]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 2. Male genitalia of species of Acrapex. – A, I. A. cuprescens (Hampson, 1910). – B, J. A. kafula le Ru sp. nov. – C, K. A. kavumba le Ru sp. nov. – D, L. A. kiakouama le Ru sp. nov. – E, M. A. malagasy Viette, 1967. – F, N. A. mediopuncta (Bowden, 1956). – G, O. A. parvaclara Berio, 1973. – H, P. A. unicolora (Hampson, 1910). Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/889489/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 2E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="17.[189,426,441,467]" box="[189,426,441,467]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,426,441,467]" fontSize="11" level="5" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" reason="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,426,441,467]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Material examined</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[189,1399,488,585]" box="[234,348,488,514]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<heading bold="true" box="[234,348,488,514]" fontSize="11" level="5" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" reason="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,348,488,514]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Holotype</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[189,1399,488,585]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
MADAGASCAR: ♂, Plateau de l’Imerina, Tananarive, Parc de Tsimbazaza, 1200 m a.s.l., 10 Oct. 1951 (MNHN, gen. prep. 4426). Several specimens are recorded by 
<bibRefCitation author="Viette P." box="[924,1083,558,585]" journalOrPublisher="Faune de Madagascar. ORSTOM-CNRS, Paris" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="394 - 417" part="20" refString="Viette P. 1967. Insectes Lepidopteres Noctuidae Amphipyrinae (Part.) et Melicleptriinae. Faune de Madagascar. ORSTOM-CNRS, Paris 20 (2): 394 - 417." title="Insectes Lepidopteres Noctuidae Amphipyrinae (Part.) et Melicleptriinae" type="journal article" year="1967">Viette (1967)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[189,1398,617,714]" box="[234,348,617,643]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<heading bold="true" box="[234,348,617,643]" fontSize="11" level="5" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" reason="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,348,617,643]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Paratype</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[189,1398,617,714]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">MADAGASCAR: 2 ♂♂, same locality and date as holotype (MNHN); 3 ♂♂, same locality as holotype, 8 Nov. 1954, P. Viette leg. (MNHN, gen. prep. 4438).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="17.[189,1351,745,818]" box="[189,334,745,771]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,334,745,771]" fontSize="11" level="5" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" reason="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,334,745,771]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[189,1351,745,818]" box="[189,1351,791,818]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
The description of the external features of the holotype by 
<bibRefCitation author="Viette P." box="[878,1033,791,818]" journalOrPublisher="Faune de Madagascar. ORSTOM-CNRS, Paris" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="394 - 417" part="20" refString="Viette P. 1967. Insectes Lepidopteres Noctuidae Amphipyrinae (Part.) et Melicleptriinae. Faune de Madagascar. ORSTOM-CNRS, Paris 20 (2): 394 - 417." title="Insectes Lepidopteres Noctuidae Amphipyrinae (Part.) et Melicleptriinae" type="journal article" year="1967">Viette (1967)</bibRefCitation>
was accurate (
<figureCitation box="[1207,1339,791,818]" captionStart="Fig. 6" captionStartId="14.[189,232,1893,1919]" captionTargetBox="[219,1361,263,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[215,1373,253,1871]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 6. Adults of species of Acrapex. – A – B. A. kavumba le Ru sp. nov. A. ♂, upper side. B. ♂, under side. – C – F. A. kiakouama le Ru sp. nov. C. ♂, upper side. D. ♂, under side. E. ♀, upper side. F. ♀, under side. – G – I. A. malagasy Viette, 1967. G. ♂, upper side. H. ♂, under side. I. ♂, original labels from MNHH. Scale bars = 10 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/889497/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 6G–H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[189,1399,849,911]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
WINGSPAN. 17–20 mm (♂♂) according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Viette P." box="[692,854,849,876]" journalOrPublisher="Faune de Madagascar. ORSTOM-CNRS, Paris" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="394 - 417" part="20" refString="Viette P. 1967. Insectes Lepidopteres Noctuidae Amphipyrinae (Part.) et Melicleptriinae. Faune de Madagascar. ORSTOM-CNRS, Paris 20 (2): 394 - 417." title="Insectes Lepidopteres Noctuidae Amphipyrinae (Part.) et Melicleptriinae" type="journal article" year="1967">Viette (1967)</bibRefCitation>
; however, only one specimen is preserved in MNHN.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[189,1399,942,1109]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
MALE GENITALIA (
<figureCitation box="[394,530,942,969]" captionStart="Fig. 2" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1873,1899]" captionTargetBox="[192,1392,424,1825]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[181,1446,419,1845]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 2. Male genitalia of species of Acrapex. – A, I. A. cuprescens (Hampson, 1910). – B, J. A. kafula le Ru sp. nov. – C, K. A. kavumba le Ru sp. nov. – D, L. A. kiakouama le Ru sp. nov. – E, M. A. malagasy Viette, 1967. – F, N. A. mediopuncta (Bowden, 1956). – G, O. A. parvaclara Berio, 1973. – H, P. A. unicolora (Hampson, 1910). Scale bars = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/889489/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 2E, M</figureCitation>
). (After 
<bibRefCitation author="Viette P." box="[634,774,942,969]" journalOrPublisher="Faune de Madagascar. ORSTOM-CNRS, Paris" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="394 - 417" part="20" refString="Viette P. 1967. Insectes Lepidopteres Noctuidae Amphipyrinae (Part.) et Melicleptriinae. Faune de Madagascar. ORSTOM-CNRS, Paris 20 (2): 394 - 417." title="Insectes Lepidopteres Noctuidae Amphipyrinae (Part.) et Melicleptriinae" type="journal article" year="1967">Viette 1967</bibRefCitation>
) Additional description: juxta large, plate-like, base slightly fattened, without sclerotization, with long and widening neck, ending on each side in rounded apex, on both sides tufted with small-sized hairs; aedeagus short, stout, not curved, with two lateral areas adorned with short setae; hand-shaped vesica with tuft of needle-shaped cornutus, pointed obliquely downward.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[189,319,1141,1167]" box="[189,319,1141,1167]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,319,1141,1167]" fontSize="11" level="5" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" reason="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,319,1141,1167]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Bionomics</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[189,408,1187,1213]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="17.[189,408,1187,1213]" box="[189,408,1187,1213]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Biology unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="17.[189,342,1245,1271]" box="[189,342,1245,1271]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,342,1245,1271]" fontSize="11" level="5" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" reason="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,342,1245,1271]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Distribution</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[189,1398,1292,1389]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
Madagascar. Only known from the type locality. The record is from secondary grassland replacing upland and montane forest (Mosaic #18) (
<bibRefCitation author="White F." box="[694,837,1327,1353]" journalOrPublisher="UNESCO, Natural Resources Research" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="1 - 356" part="20" refString="White F. 1983. The vegetation of Africa, a descriptive memoir to accompany the UNESCO / AETFAT / UNSO vegetation map of Africa. UNESCO, Natural Resources Research 20: 1 - 356." title="The vegetation of Africa, a descriptive memoir to accompany the UNESCO / AETFAT / UNSO vegetation map of Africa" type="journal article" year="1983">White 1983</bibRefCitation>
) (
<figureCitation box="[864,938,1327,1353]" captionStart="Fig. 4" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1999,2025]" captionTargetBox="[192,1398,954,1963]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[98,1406,944,1972]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 4. Distribution map of sampled specimens of Acrapex Hampson, 1891." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/889493/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
), belonging to the Sudanian bioregion (
<bibRefCitation author="Linder H. P. &amp; de Klerk H. M. &amp; Born J. &amp; Burgess N. D. &amp; Fjeldsa J. &amp; Rahbek C." box="[197,410,1362,1389]" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Biogeography" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="1189 - 1205" part="39" publicationUrl="http://dx.doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-2699.2012.02728.x" refString="Linder H. P., de Klerk H. M., Born J., Burgess N. D., Fjeldsa J. &amp; Rahbek C. 2012. The partitioning of Africa: statistically defned biogeographical regions in sub-Saharan Africa. Journal of Biogeography 39: 1189 - 1205. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2699.2012.02728. x" title="The partitioning of Africa: statistically defned biogeographical regions in sub-Saharan Africa" type="journal article" year="2012">
Linder 
<emphasis box="[284,336,1362,1388]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">et al</emphasis>
. 2012
</bibRefCitation>
) (
<figureCitation box="[435,507,1362,1389]" captionStart="Fig. 5" captionStartId="12.[189,232,1999,2025]" captionTargetBox="[184,1401,1365,1961]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[130,1445,1353,1974]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 5. Major bioregions, modifed after Linder et al. (2012)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/889495/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
